To create a tidier display, order or person information should only be shown when an order or person command is executed respectively.
Let's separate the information being displayed in ReadyBakey depending on what command type the user is requesting for.

This means CommandResult needs to have an additional input parameters to establish the command type. Thereafter, this will be used to determine what information is to be displayed.

commitResults.messageBody:
Let's create feature to sort orders by delivery date to improve user's ability to prioritise orders

Because ModelManager handles the output of orders that are being shown in the frontend, this is where the changes begin.
The order list that is returned out must be generalised to a ObservableList as it no longer can only be FilteredList, as it could be a SortedList.

Any method that requires a sorting command can call the new updatedSortedFilteredOrderList. Such is the case for FindIncompleteOrdersCommand.
